# CLI Commands and Utility Scripts

LocalCA-Go provides several utility scripts and commands to help with development, testing, and deployment.

## Development Scripts

- [run-dev.sh](mdc:run-dev.sh) / [run-dev.bat](mdc:run-dev.bat) - Start the application in development mode
  ```bash
  # On Unix-based systems
  ./run-dev.sh
  
  # On Windows
  ./run-dev.bat
  ```

- [run-tests.sh](mdc:run-tests.sh) / [run-tests.bat](mdc:run-tests.bat) - Run the test suite
  ```bash
  # On Unix-based systems
  ./run-tests.sh
  
  # On Windows
  ./run-tests.bat
  ```

- [run-security-scan.sh](mdc:run-security-scan.sh) / [run-security-scan.bat](mdc:run-security-scan.bat) - Run security scanning tools
  ```bash
  # On Unix-based systems
  ./run-security-scan.sh
  
  # On Windows
  ./run-security-scan.bat
  ```

## Docker Commands

- Build and start services:
  ```bash
  docker-compose up -d
  ```

- Build images only:
  ```bash
  docker-compose build
  ```

- View logs:
  ```bash
  docker-compose logs -f
  ```

- Stop services:
  ```bash
  docker-compose down
  ```

## Go Commands

- Run the application:
  ```bash
  go run main.go
  ```

- Run tests:
  ```bash
  go test ./...
  ```

- Build the application:
  ```bash
  go build -o localca
  ```

## Frontend Commands

- Start development server:
  ```bash
  npm run dev
  # or
  pnpm dev
  ```

- Build for production:
  ```bash
  npm run build
  # or
  pnpm build
  ```

- Run tests:
  ```bash
  npm test
  # or
  pnpm test
  ```
